      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): cache provider tool schema normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Cache provider-normalized tool schema `parameters` for repeated embedded agent turns when the active provider hook exposes a stable hook-owned cache key.\n- Keep the cache conservative: the key includes provider hook identity plus provider/model/runtime inputs and ordered original tool schema signatures; cached values clone only tool `parameters`, not tool objects, execute closures, approval state, or guards.\n- Add `OPENCLAW_TOOL_SCHEMA_CACHE=0` as a kill switch, SDK docs/API surface for `resolveToolSchemaCacheKey`, and focused cache-key, clone-safety, env-disable, eviction, and runtime-handle coverage.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: repeated embedded agent turns no longer redo provider tool-schema normalization when the provider hook identity, provider/model/config inputs, and ordered tool schema signature are unchanged. Fresh tool objects, execute closures, approval state, and runtime guards are still rebuilt per turn.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `tool-schema-cache-pr3`, current head `98e63ff4a9e4d5e357b34ae20a07c79d510a09dc`, rebased onto latest `origin/main` at `ec2455a842cfc038fa8551415dcc20d177257ab7`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Rebased the branch onto current `origin/main`, regenerated the plugin SDK API baseline from the merged tree, ran the focused schema/runtime/doctor tests, checked the generated SDK API baseline, linted the touched TypeScript files, checked markdown/docs indexing, and verified whitespace/conflict markers with `git diff --check`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nnode --max-old-space-size=8192 --import tsx scripts/generate-plugin-sdk-api-baseline.ts --write\nWrote docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\nWrote docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.json (gitignored, local only)\nWrote docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.jsonl (gitignored, local only)\n\nnode --max-old-space-size=8192 --import tsx scripts/generate-plugin-sdk-api-baseline.ts --check\nOK docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-schema-runtime.test.ts src/agents/runtime-plan/build.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime-errors.test.ts\n4 Vitest shards passed: 6 files / 123 tests\n\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-schema-runtime.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-schema-runtime.test.ts src/agents/openai-transport-stream.test.ts src/agents/runtime-plan/build.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime-errors.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/plugin-entry.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/plugins/provider-hook-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts src/plugins/types.ts\nexit 0\n\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\nexit 0\n\nnode scripts/docs-list.js\nexit 0\n\ngit merge-tree --write-tree origin/main HEAD\nexit 0\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the provider schema-normalization cache stores normalized parameters once and reuses cloned parameters on subsequent matching calls while preserving fresh tool closures. Regression coverage also proves cache keys are resolved from the same prepared provider runtime handle used for normalization, preventing cross-plugin reuse.\n\nWhat was not tested: full live-provider end-to-end latency was not tested. This PR caches only provider-normalized schema `parameters`; it does not cache complete tool inventory/materialization, policy resolution, prompt inputs, or full agent-turn startup.\n",
